The **Email Human Task** provides an interface to write and send an email from within the Workplace 2 task editor.

## Interface
![](data:image/png;base64,)Email Human Task in the task editor of Workplace 2

## Configuration
The configuration of a Human Task is done in Process Designer. It consists of three mappings:

- **General parameters:** General properties of the Human Task

- **Input parameters:** Defines the input data which will be consumed by Process Engine

- **Output parameters:** Defines the output data which will be exposed to the user and/or the system

The individual fields for each parameter group are described in detail below.

### General task parameters
All Human Task types require general task parameters. These general parameters are described in [Workplace 2 Human Tasks](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1).

![](data:image/png;base64,)Configuration window for general task parameters in Process Designer

### Input parameters
In addition to the [basic input parameters](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-input-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the Email Human Task also requires the following type-specific input parameters:

Field

Type

Mandatory or optional

Values

Description

`to`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

String with To email address to be pre-filled. Use `,` to separate multiple addresses.

`cc`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

String with Cc email address to be pre-filled. Use `,` to separate multiple addresses.

`bcc`

text/plain

Optional

0..n

String with Bcc email address to be pre-filled. Use `,` to separate multiple addresses.

`isCcVisible`

x-xsd/boolean

Optional

- `true` 

- `false`

Specifies if the Cc field is displayed in the human task.

`isBccVisible`

x-xsd/boolean

Optional

- `true` 

- `false`

Specifies if the Bcc field is displayed in the human task.

`subject`

text/plain

Optional

0..1

The email's subject line.

`text`

text/plain

Optional

0..1

Plain text body that may include HTML tags.

`isTextVisible`

x-xsd/boolean

Optional

- `true` 

- `false`

Controls whether the text field is visible.

### Output parameters
In addition to the [basic output parameters](https://docs.doxee.com/doxee-platform/docs/workplace-2-6-6-human-tasks-1#basic-output-parameters) common to all Human Task types, the Email Human Task also requires the following type-specific output parameters:

Field

Type

Values

Description

`to`

text/plain

0..n

Chosen 'To' address.

`bcc`

text/plain

0..n

Chosen 'Bcc' address

`cc`

text/plain

0..n

Chosen 'Cc' address

`subject`

text/plain

0..1

Chosen 'Subject'

`text`

text/plain

0..1

Chosen plain text body.

Process Designer is a GUI tool for creating and testing Infinica Process Definitions (IPD). It&#39;s a support tool for Process Engine, providing a graphical editing and log interface and removing the necessity to manually write XML processes in a text editor.
